<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="072" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4">
  <metadata>
    <title>A.2: Tighten WorkspaceRendererWebApi to require IWebApi methods (Path 2a, no wrapper)</title>
    <phase>6.5: R4 add-on cleanup</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>1.5</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>052</dependencies>
    <blocks>none</blocks>
    <tags>frontend, typescript, refactoring, shared-lib</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Code refactor on shared library interface used by LegalWorkspace renderer. Static type tightening with cast removal. FULL per Step 3.5.5 (modifies code with ADR-012 constraint + downstream-revealing nature).</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>K</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Touches @spaarke/ui-components/workspace/ only — different files from 073, 074, 075, 076, 077</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Operator decision 2026-05-27 (Path 2a): instead of the wrapper component originally proposed,
    tighten WorkspaceRendererWebApi to REQUIRE the methods that IWebApi requires. Drop the
    `LegalWorkspaceApp as unknown as WorkspaceRenderer` cast. TypeScript proves correctness
    statically — no runtime wrapper, no architectural debt for fictional flexibility.

    Rationale: per operator architectural direction, LegalWorkspace IS the dashboard renderer;
    new dashboard pieces are added INSIDE that library, not as separate renderers. The
    "many renderers, each with different method needs" use case that motivated the loose
    interface doesn't exist and won't exist.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE TypeScript developer. Variance-literate. Bias toward honest type contracts over
    static-type lies. Per-cast commit discipline (this task is ONE focused commit).
  </role>

  <goal>
    (1) `WorkspaceRendererWebApi` (in `@spaarke/ui-components/workspace/`) tightened from
    all-optional methods to `Pick<IWebApi, 'createRecord' | 'retrieveRecord' |
    'retrieveMultipleRecords' | 'updateRecord' | 'deleteRecord'>` — methods REQUIRED.
    (2) `LegalWorkspaceApp as unknown as WorkspaceRenderer` cast REMOVED at its call site
    (find via grep). (3) `tsc --noEmit` passes on `@spaarke/ui-components` AND on
    `@spaarke/legal-workspace` (the consumer). (4) No new wrapper component introduced.
    (5) Existing tests pass.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Task 052 (C-4) introduced the WorkspaceRenderer interface to decouple `LegalWorkspaceApp`
      from being hard-wired as the only renderer. To make the interface generic, methods on
      `WorkspaceRendererWebApi` were marked OPTIONAL. But `LegalWorkspaceApp` expects strict
      `IWebApi` (methods REQUIRED). TypeScript's contravariance correctly refuses the assignment
      (loose-to-strict is unsafe), forcing a `LegalWorkspaceApp as unknown as WorkspaceRenderer`
      cast.

      Operator decision 2026-05-27: the loose-interface flexibility was for a fictional use case
      (multiple renderers with different method needs). Going forward, LegalWorkspace IS the
      renderer; new dashboard pieces are added INSIDE that library. So tighten the interface to
      reflect reality.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/workspace/WorkspaceRenderer.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/workspace/defaultWorkspaceRenderer.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/WorkspaceLayoutWidget.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/__tests__/WorkspaceLayoutWidget.test.tsx</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Shared components live in `@spaarke/*` lib family and remain context-agnostic.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">NO wrapper component. The fix is interface tightening only. If a wrapper appears in the diff, STOP — that's not the approved approach.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">NO new abstractions. Use TypeScript's `Pick<IWebApi, '...' | '...'>` utility type — that's the entire fix.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Remove the cast `as unknown as WorkspaceRenderer` everywhere. Grep first to find all call sites.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Existing tests at `__tests__/WorkspaceLayoutWidget.test.tsx` MUST continue to pass.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 only.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-022-react-19-code-pages.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/c4-interface-design.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/r5-backlog-candidates.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Inspect current state">Read `WorkspaceRenderer.ts` and `defaultWorkspaceRenderer.ts`. Identify the `WorkspaceRendererWebApi` interface definition. Note all methods marked optional.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Grep cast sites">Run `grep -rn "as unknown as WorkspaceRenderer\|as WorkspaceRenderer" --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx" src/`. Catalog every match. Expected: at least 1 site in WorkspaceLayoutWidget.tsx.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Tighten the interface">Edit `WorkspaceRenderer.ts`: change `WorkspaceRendererWebApi` from manually-listed optional methods to `Pick&lt;IWebApi, 'createRecord' | 'retrieveRecord' | 'retrieveMultipleRecords' | 'updateRecord' | 'deleteRecord'&gt;`. Import `IWebApi` from wherever it's defined in the legal-workspace shared lib (likely `@spaarke/legal-workspace` types or `@spaarke/ui-components/types`).</step>
    <step order="4" name="Remove all casts">For each cast site from step 2: remove the `as unknown as WorkspaceRenderer` cast. TypeScript should now accept the assignment directly.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Typecheck verification">Run `npx tsc --noEmit` on `@spaarke/ui-components` AND on `@spaarke/legal-workspace` AND on `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/` (the consumer code page). All 0 errors.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Test verification">Run `npm test` in `@spaarke/ui-components`. The WorkspaceLayoutWidget tests must pass. If new failures appear, they are likely a sign the interface change is wider than expected — ESCALATE.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Document in notes">Write `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/072-workspace-renderer-fix.md` summarizing: cast sites removed, interface diff, test results, any downstream surprises.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Inspect WorkspaceRenderer.ts + consumer files</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Find all cast sites</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Tighten interface + remove casts</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">tsc --noEmit, npm test</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/workspace/WorkspaceRenderer.ts (modified — interface tightened)</output>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/WorkspaceLayoutWidget.tsx (modified — cast removed)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/072-workspace-renderer-fix.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the interface change, When `WorkspaceRendererWebApi` is inspected, Then methods are REQUIRED (no `?:` markers) and the type is expressed via `Pick&lt;IWebApi, ...&gt;`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the cast removal, When `grep -rn "as unknown as WorkspaceRenderer\|as WorkspaceRenderer"` runs across `src/`, Then 0 matches in production code.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the change, When `npx tsc --noEmit` runs on `@spaarke/ui-components`, `@spaarke/legal-workspace`, and `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/`, Then all 0 errors.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the change, When `npm test` runs in `@spaarke/ui-components`, Then WorkspaceLayoutWidget tests pass.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the change, When the diff is inspected, Then NO new wrapper component appears.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Per operator decision 2026-05-27 — the wrapper approach is REJECTED. This is the entire fix:
    one interface tightening + cast removal at call sites. If the work expands beyond that
    scope, STOP and report.

    Pairs naturally with task 074 (UI.Components 24 tsc errors) since both touch the same
    package's types. But they're in different files — parallel-safe.
  </notes>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <protocol>FULL rigor — Step 9.5 quality gates (code-review + adr-check) after implementation. Checkpointing every 3 steps.</protocol>
